Launch centos image OS from docker hub
# docker pull centos:7  --> This will pull the image of centos:7 from docker.hub website
Launch a  new container OS named futrons
# docker run -it  --name futrons centos:7
To stop use 
# docker stop futrons
To start again use these 2 commands
# docker start futrons
# docker attach futrons

now you can use this conatiner agagin and again for use with same permannet data.

to remove conatiner
# docker remove futrons

to remove image
# docker rmi centos:7
